# MY Stack App — Project Context

## Stack
- **FastAPI** — async Python web framework
- **SQLModel** — ORM (SQLAlchemy + Pydantic; models are also API schemas)
- **Alembic** — database migrations
- **Jinja2** — server-side HTML templates
- **Bootstrap 5** — frontend styling
- **Postgres** — primary database
- **Redis** — caching / background tasks
- **Gunicorn + Uvicorn workers** — production server
- **AWS CDK (TypeScript)** — infrastructure as code
- **Docker Compose** — local development
- **uv** — Python package manager (`pyproject.toml`; use `uv run`, `uv add`, `uv sync`)

## Project Structure
```
app/
  main.py        # FastAPI app factory
  config.py      # Settings (pydantic-settings, reads .env)
  database.py    # SQLModel engine + get_session dependency
  models/        # SQLModel table models
  routers/       # APIRouter modules
  templates/     # Jinja2 HTML templates
  static/        # CSS, JS, images
alembic/         # Migration scripts
infrastructure/  # AWS CDK (TypeScript)
.github/         # CI/CD workflows
```

## General Conventions
- Use `async def` for all route handlers and DB operations
- Settings always come from `app/config.py` (never hardcode secrets)
- All DB access via the `get_session` dependency — never create sessions manually
- Raise `HTTPException` with meaningful status codes; never return bare dicts for errors
- Keep routers thin — business logic goes in service functions or model methods
- Environment variables defined in `.env.example`; actual `.env` is gitignored
